OL,6,FA police officer who assaulted a
OL,7,Fteenager who had subjected him to
OL,8,F'sustained homophobic abuse' in
OL,9,Fcustody has been allowed to keep his
OL,10,Fjob.
OL,12,FPolice Constable Samuel Clarke faced a
OL,13,FCheshire Police misconduct hearing,
OL,14,Fwhere it was ruled that his actions
OL,15,Fdid amount to gross misconduct.
OL,17,FAs a result he was handed a final
OL,18,Fwritten warning by the force, allowing
OL,19,Fhim to keep his job.
