OL,3,CPolice officer assaulted teen who
OL,4,Csubjected him homophobic abuse
OL,6,FThe officer then "used force against
OL,7,Fthe juvenile, which was not deemed to
OL,8,Fbe reasonable, necessary, or
OL,9,Fproportionate".
OL,11,FPC Clarke was later charged with
OL,12,Fassault by beating and subsequently
OL,13,Fconvicted following a trial at Sefton
OL,14,FMagistrates' Court.
OL,16,FHe appeared back before the court in
OL,17,FOctober to be sentenced to an 18-month
OL,18,Fcommunity order, including 200 hours
OL,19,Fof unpaid community work and 20
OL,20,Frehabilitation activity requirement
OL,21,Fdays.
